Preconditions:
- The input grid must be a 2D array of integers.
- The grid must have at least one row and one column.
- The values in the grid must be non-negative integers.

Postconditions:
- The method should return an integer representing the minimum time required to visit the bottom-right cell of the matrix.
- If it is not possible to visit the bottom-right cell, the method should return -1.